htref:CIM htref:description "The Common Information Model (CIM) is a formal object-oriented schema developed by the Distributed Management Task Force (DMTF) to represent managed elements in IT environments, including computer systems, racks, chassis, processors, memory, power supplies, networking components, and cooling subsystems. CIM provides a strong reference model for AI Factory physical and logical infrastructure components." .
